# Memory Bank: ludovicozizzo.github.io (al-folio theme)

## Repository Overview
This is a personal academic website built with the **al-folio** Jekyll theme, hosted on GitHub Pages.

## Key Configuration Files

### `_config.yml` - Main configuration
- **Site settings**: `first_name`, `last_name`, `description`, `url`
- **Layout settings**: `navbar_fixed`, `footer_fixed`, `search_enabled`
- **Search controls**: `posts_in_search`, `socials_in_search`, `bib_search`
- **Scholar settings**: `scholar.last_name`, `scholar.first_name` for publication author highlighting

### Removing/Hiding Content
The easiest way to remove pages/features without deleting files is to add them to the `exclude:` section in `_config.yml`:

### Key Pages Location
- `_pages/about.md` - Home page (permalink: /)
- `_pages/cv.md` - CV page
- `_pages/teaching.md` - Teaching page
- `_pages/publications.md` - Publications page (uses Jekyll Scholar)

### About Page Front Matter Options
```yaml
selected_papers: false  # Show/hide selected papers section
social: false           # Show/hide social icons
announcements:
  enabled: false        # Show/hide news section
latest_posts:
  enabled: false        # Show/hide blog posts
```

### Teaching Page Format
Best formatted with markdown tables:
```markdown
| Term | Course |
|:-----|:-------|
| Spring 2026 | Course Name |
```

## Profile Image
- Located at `assets/img/zizzo_pic.jpg`
- Configured in `_pages/about.md` under `profile.image`

## Navigation Order
Set `nav_order: N` in page front matter to control navbar order.
